==English==
Through Old French from Latin ''[[rubrica]]'' (red ochre), the substance used to make red letters.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# a [[heading]] in a book [[highlight]]ed in [[red]]
# an established [[rule]] or [[custom]], a [[guideline]]
# a [[category]] or [[classification]]
#:*That would fall under the '''rubric''' of things we can ignore for now.
# (''Education'') a printed set of [[score|scoring]] [[criteria]] for evaluating student work and for giving feedback

